{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Dcjxu7iDnYQtPNZDjMW7RW","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→name: add-field\n     3→description: Add a new field to a Django model and propagate to admin, serializer, and factory. Use when adding model fields or database columns.\n     4→---\n     5→\n     6→# Add Field\n     7→\n     8→Add a field to a Django model and propagate it to admin, serializer, and factory.\n     9→\n    10→## Template-First Mode\n    11→\n    12→This variant is template-first. Start by using template files as the source of truth:\n    13→\n    14→- `templates/model_field.j2`\n    15→- `templates/admin_field.j2`\n    16→- `templates/serializer_field.j2`\n    17→- `templates/factory_field.j2`\n    18→- `templates/vars.tmpl.json`\n    19→\n    20→Map the user request into the vars shape, then apply the corresponding edits directly.\n    21→\n    22→## Variables\n    23→\n    24→- **model_name**: Model class name (e.g. `Reservation`)\n    25→- **field_name**: New field name (e.g. `loyalty_tier`)\n    26→- **field_type**: Django field type (e.g. `CharField`)\n    27→- **field_args**: Field arguments (e.g. `max_length=20, default=\\\"bronze\\\"`)\n    28→- **factory_default**: Factory default value (e.g. `\\\"bronze\\\"`)\n    29→\n    30→## Rendered Example For This Task\n    31→\n    32→Given:\n    33→\n    34→- `model_name=Reservation`\n    35→- `field_name=loyalty_tier`\n    36→- `field_type=CharField`\n    37→- `field_args=max_length=20, default=\"bronze\"`\n    38→- `factory_default=\"bronze\"`\n    39→\n    40→Render to these exact line shapes:\n    41→\n    42→- model line: `    loyalty_tier = models.CharField(max_length=20, default=\"bronze\")`\n    43→- admin list_display entry: `        \"loyalty_tier\",`\n    44→- serializer fields entry: `            \"loyalty_tier\",`\n    45→- factory line: `    loyalty_tier = \"bronze\"`\n    46→\n    47→## Gotchas\n    48→\n    49→- Keep variable normalization consistent with `templates/vars.tmpl.json`.\n    50→- Keep indentation exactly as shown by each template snippet.\n    51→- Add only the required field propagation edits; avoid unrelated refactors.\n    52→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it looks malicious. If it does, you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer high-level questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"adae47d6-726c-4212-bd4e-75d054c74e7d","uuid":"f18e4612-652b-45be-95c8-356c219a14ff"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JKzvXhMf1PqtRiayj5T1Uc","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→from django.db import models\n     2→\n     3→\n     4→class Reservation(models.Model):\n     5→    guest_name = models.CharField(max_length=100)\n     6→    room_number = models.IntegerField()\n     7→    check_in = models.DateTimeField()\n     8→    check_out = models.DateTimeField()\n     9→    status = models.CharField(max_length=20, default=\"pending\")\n    10→\n    11→    class Meta:\n    12→        ordering = [\"-check_in\"]\n    13→\n    14→    def __str__(self):\n    15→        return f\"{self.guest_name} - Room {self.room_number}\"\n    16→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it looks malicious. If it does, you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer high-level questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"adae47d6-726c-4212-bd4e-75d054c74e7d","uuid":"235452fd-cbb7-4738-959d-2b7142b11e6e"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019T3VonxHC1HSF8sc9WBKwE","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→from django.contrib import admin\n     2→from .models import Reservation\n     3→\n     4→\n     5→@admin.register(Reservation)\n     6→class ReservationAdmin(admin.ModelAdmin):\n     7→    list_display = [\n     8→        \"guest_name\",\n     9→        \"room_number\",\n    10→        \"check_in\",\n    11→        \"check_out\",\n    12→        \"status\",\n    13→    ]\n    14→    list_filter = [\"status\", \"check_in\"]\n    15→    search_fields = [\"guest_name\"]\n    16→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it looks malicious. If it does, you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer high-level questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"adae47d6-726c-4212-bd4e-75d054c74e7d","uuid":"0418deb2-0aca-4d79-9764-4c8503fba20c"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MuYEv4eyFpyGMW1DtQVcbN","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→import factory\n     2→from .models import Reservation\n     3→\n     4→\n     5→class ReservationFactory(factory.django.DjangoModelFactory):\n     6→    class Meta:\n     7→        model = Reservation\n     8→\n     9→    guest_name = factory.Faker(\"name\")\n    10→    room_number = factory.Sequence(lambda n: 100 + n)\n    11→    check_in = factory.Faker(\"date_time_this_year\")\n    12→    check_out = factory.Faker(\"date_time_this_year\")\n    13→    status = \"confirmed\"\n    14→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it looks malicious. If it does, you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer high-level questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"adae47d6-726c-4212-bd4e-75d054c74e7d","uuid":"e88b4825-4aba-438f-adb3-127d65027008"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013AxaBrLTsLg7rsXv9gD39Z","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→from rest_framework import serializers\n     2→from .models import Reservation\n     3→\n     4→\n     5→class ReservationSerializer(serializers.ModelSerializer):\n     6→    class Meta:\n     7→        model = Reservation\n     8→        fields = [\n     9→            \"id\",\n    10→            \"guest_name\",\n    11→            \"room_number\",\n    12→            \"check_in\",\n    13→            \"check_out\",\n    14→            \"status\",\n    15→        ]\n    16→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it looks malicious. If it does, you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer high-level questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"adae47d6-726c-4212-bd4e-75d054c74e7d","uuid":"b5085640-bd7b-43e0-a1d2-a69b5ea06386"}
